article.description: — Cam Spencer had 25 points as Loyola (Md.) narrowly beat American 78-73 on Saturday.
article.headline: Spencer scores 25 to lift Loyola (Md.) past American 78-73
article.linkText: Spencer scores 25 to lift Loyola (Md.) past American 78-73
article.story: BALTIMORE -- — Cam Spencer had 25 points as Loyola (Md.) narrowly beat American 78-73 on Saturday. Spencer hit 4 of 6 3-pointers. Jaylin Andrews had 17 points for Loyola (Md.) (12-7, 6-2 Patriot League). Kenneth Jones added 10 points and seven assists. Milos Ilic had 10 points. Connor Nelson scored a career-high 23 points for the Eagles (5-12, 1-4). Matt Rogers added 13 points. Stacy Beckton Jr. had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
